# Use an official Python runtime as a parent image
FROM python:3.8-slim

# Set the working directory in the container
WORKDIR /app

# Copy the entire repository into the container
COPY . /app/

# Install system dependencies for building spaCy from source
RUN apt-get update && \
    apt-get install -y build-essential python-dev git && \
    apt-get clean && \
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

# Create a virtual environment and activate it, ensuring the latest pip is used
RUN python -m venv .env && \
    ./.env/bin/activate && \
    python -m pip install -U pip setuptools wheel

# Install the required Python dependencies
RUN pip install -r requirements.txt

# Install spaCy in editable mode
RUN pip install --no-build-isolation --editable .

# Run the test suite to verify the installation
RUN pytest
